\begin{align}
  \dfrac{dy}{dx}&= \dfrac{d}{dx}(x^3-11x+5) = 1\\
  \implies 3x^2-11&= 1\implies x^2 = 4\text{ or }x=\pm 2
\end{align}
\\ \text{The two tangents with slope 1 are therefore,}\\
\begin{tabular}{cccc}
x& y& m& \text{Line} \\
-2& 19& 1&\frac{y+2}{x-19}=1\implies y=x-21\\
2& -9& 1&\frac{y+9}{x-2}=1\implies y=x-11
\end{tabular}
\\ \text{Hence, the required point is }(2,-9).

